flenstag - Flickr Lens Tagger
=============================

flenstag scans photos from Flickr and adds appropriate tags generated
from the EXIF data of the photos. The default configuration tags:

    camera model,
    lens model,
    ISO speed,
    focal length and
    exposure time
    aperture fnumber

retrieved from the EXIF data.

flenstag is written in Perl and requires Flickr::API. The script saves
runtime data and expects the configuration file in the current directory:

    flenstag.conf: configuration file
    flenstag.dat : tracks upload dates (might be used for filtering)
    flenstag.auth: Flickr API authentication

The flenstag.conf must exist before running flenstag (take
flenstag.conf.ex as a template).
